INSERT INTO public.questions (exam_id, subject_id, topic_id, year, paper, question_text, option_1, option_2, option_3, option_4, correct_option, explanation, difficulty) VALUES
('e33338c9-740c-48c4-914b-2cca3e9c1668'::uuid, '637bf719-8dde-4035-946c-4242372328e2'::uuid, '29d611e8-8d9c-48f0-85c3-621cccd58722'::uuid, 2023, 'Paper-I', '______ is the number of vehicles occupying a unit length of a lane of roadway at given instant.', 'Traffic Capacity', 'Basic Capacity', 'Traffic Density', 'Traffic Volume', 3, 'Traffic density is vehicles per unit length.', 'medium'),
('e33338c9-740c-48c4-914b-2cca3e9c1668'::uuid, 'c542f294-548d-4129-8d45-b3f75629dc1b'::uuid, '5005286a-c8a9-4f38-a12f-46a61fd65689'::uuid, 2023, 'Paper-I', 'The maximum permissible limit for fluoride in drinking water is', '1.5 mg/liter', '0.1 mg/liter', '5 mg/liter', '10 mg/liter', 1, 'As per IS 10500, fluoride limit is 1.5 mg/l.', 'medium'),
('e33338c9-740c-48c4-914b-2cca3e9c1668'::uuid, '3f275622-18e3-40ce-a134-ec660b48190c'::uuid, 'f28c858a-cf0c-482e-a112-8845927e82f4'::uuid, 2023, 'Paper-I', 'Total station only measures', 'Horizontal angles only', 'Vertical angles only', 'Slope distances only', 'Horizontal, and vertical angles and slope distances', 4, 'Total station measures all three.', 'medium'),
('e33338c9-740c-48c4-914b-2cca3e9c1668'::uuid, 'dd2eab18-a6c2-4636-a005-1f9ea9aef419'::uuid, '4002ff85-6eee-4cd3-8c35-1d7039df2745'::uuid, 2023, 'Paper-I', 'A column pinned supports with length L has the radius of gyration r. The modulus of elasticity is E. The critical stress of the simply supported column due to the Euler critical load can be given by:', '4π² E r² / L²', 'π² E r² / (2L²)', 'π² E r² / L²', '2.046 π² E r² / L²', 3, 'Critical stress = π² E / (L/r)² = π² E r² / L².', 'medium'),
('e33338c9-740c-48c4-914b-2cca3e9c1668'::uuid, 'c542f294-548d-4129-8d45-b3f75629dc1b'::uuid, '5005286a-c8a9-4f38-a12f-46a61fd65689'::uuid, 2023, 'Paper-I', 'The amount of coagulant needed for coagulation of water increases with A. Increase in turbidity of water B. Decrease in turbidity of water C. Increase in temperature of water D. Decrease in temperature of water The correct answer is', 'A and D', 'A and B', 'B and C', 'B and D', 1, 'Coagulant demand increases with turbidity and decreases with temperature (i.e., increases when temperature decreases).', 'medium'),
('e33338c9-740c-48c4-914b-2cca3e9c1668'::uuid, 'c39bc91d-4a88-42c6-b1f7-ae4fc2b0dba1'::uuid, '4c395c9a-2cad-4ea6-ac3d-b0b7bd1a4dee'::uuid, 2023, 'Paper-I', 'Specific gravity of solids is the ratio of', 'Bulk unit weight of soil to unit weight of water', 'Unit weight of solids to unit weight of water', 'Unit weight of water to Bulk unit weight of soil', 'Unit weight of solids to Bulk unit weight of soil', 2, 'G = γ_s / γ_w.', 'medium'),
('e33338c9-740c-48c4-914b-2cca3e9c1668'::uuid, '637bf719-8dde-4035-946c-4242372328e2'::uuid, '29d611e8-8d9c-48f0-85c3-621cccd58722'::uuid, 2023, 'Paper-I', 'The shape of the STOP signs according to IRC: 67-2001 is', 'Octagonal', 'Rectangular', 'Circular', 'Triangular', 1, 'STOP sign is octagonal.', 'medium'),
('e33338c9-740c-48c4-914b-2cca3e9c1668'::uuid, 'a3efd61d-542a-4076-8ffe-631b227f0239'::uuid, '880c7ee1-0204-4a42-979f-338ca32f84be'::uuid, 2023, 'Paper-I', 'Consider the following statements A. At high temperature plastic materials exhibits good stiffness, whereas at low temperature their hardness and strength increases. B. Plastic materials can be made ductile through blending process of fabrication. Choose the correct option', 'Statement B is false, and A is true', 'Statement B is true, and A is false', 'Both A and B are false', 'Both A and B are true', 3, 'A is false (plastics soften at high temp); B is false (blending does not make them ductile).', 'medium'),
('e33338c9-740c-48c4-914b-2cca3e9c1668'::uuid, '3f275622-18e3-40ce-a134-ec660b48190c'::uuid, 'f28c858a-cf0c-482e-a112-8845927e82f4'::uuid, 2023, 'Paper-I', 'A surveyor measured the distance between two points marked on the plan to a scale of 1 cm = 1 m (RF=1:100) and found it to be 40 m. Later he detected that he used the wrong scale of 1:50. Determine the correct length in meters.', '90', '100', '80', '70', 3, 'Correct length = measured × (100/50) = 80 m.', 'medium'),
('e33338c9-740c-48c4-914b-2cca3e9c1668'::uuid, 'dd2eab18-a6c2-4636-a005-1f9ea9aef419'::uuid, '4002ff85-6eee-4cd3-8c35-1d7039df2745'::uuid, 2023, 'Paper-I', 'Which of the following statements is/are correct? A. The stiffness of an axially loaded prismatic bar is inversely proportional to the length of the bar. B. The stiffness of an axially loaded prismatic bar is inversely proportional to the cross-sectional area of the bar. C. The flexibility of an axially loaded prismatic bar is inversely proportional to the length of the bar. D. The flexibility of an axially loaded prismatic bar is inversely proportional to the cross-sectional area of the bar. Choose the correct option', 'B and C', 'A and C', 'B and D', 'A and D', 4, 'Stiffness = AE/L (inversely proportional to L); flexibility = L/(AE) (inversely proportional to A).', 'medium'),
('e33338c9-740c-48c4-914b-2cca3e9c1668'::uuid, 'aee3c24f-8b41-461f-8e64-e9544a04c1b6'::uuid, '4cf00bbd-c0d6-49dd-88a5-505bae0ef9ab'::uuid, 2023, 'Paper-I', 'Inner dimension of a room are 5×4 m with 40 cm wall thickness, The central line length will be :', '19.6 m', '21.8 m', '20.0 m', '21.4 m', 1, 'Centre line length = 2×(5+4) + 4×t? Actually = 2×(5+0.4+4+0.4) = 2×9.8 = 19.6 m.', 'medium'),
('e33338c9-740c-48c4-914b-2cca3e9c1668'::uuid, 'dd2eab18-a6c2-4636-a005-1f9ea9aef419'::uuid, '4002ff85-6eee-4cd3-8c35-1d7039df2745'::uuid, 2023, 'Paper-I', 'For a cantilever beam of length L with a clockwise moment M at its free end, the maximum bending moment will occur at :', 'Free end only', 'Fixed support only', 'At the centre only', 'Throughout the span L', 4, 'Moment is constant throughout the span.', 'medium'),
('e33338c9-740c-48c4-914b-2cca3e9c1668'::uuid, 'c542f294-548d-4129-8d45-b3f75629dc1b'::uuid, '5005286a-c8a9-4f38-a12f-46a61fd65689'::uuid, 2023, 'Paper-I', 'The dissolved oxygen level in natural unpolluted waters at normal temperature is found to be of the order of', '10 mg/liter', '1 mg/liter', '100 mg/liter', '1000 mg/liter', 1, 'Typical DO ≈ 10 mg/l.', 'medium'),
('e33338c9-740c-48c4-914b-2cca3e9c1668'::uuid, 'cd7b170d-eba3-4a13-8b23-3c318071b538'::uuid, '63b1aa41-9022-4bff-b5b8-0aa71ec874fd'::uuid, 2023, 'Paper-I', 'What is the effective throat thickness of fillet weld size 6 mm if the angle between fusion faces is 110° ?', '3.90 mm', '4.20 mm', '3.30 mm', '3.60 mm', Unknown, 'Formula: throat = size × sin(θ/2) = 6×sin55° = 4.91 mm, not matching options; likely a different interpretation.', 'medium'),
('e33338c9-740c-48c4-914b-2cca3e9c1668'::uuid, 'c542f294-548d-4129-8d45-b3f75629dc1b'::uuid, '5005286a-c8a9-4f38-a12f-46a61fd65689'::uuid, 2023, 'Paper-I', 'Which one of the following is NOT a sewer appurtenance ?', 'Septic Tank', 'Flushing Tank', 'Manhole', 'Grease and Oil trap', 1, 'Septic tank is a treatment unit, not a sewer appurtenance.', 'medium'),
('e33338c9-740c-48c4-914b-2cca3e9c1668'::uuid, 'a8556419-0986-4502-80b2-78b7defb8990'::uuid, 'ec71764c-6040-47e0-bbc1-9777aafbeec7'::uuid, 2023, 'Paper-I', 'In steady flow through a pipe the density, velocity and area of a section are 3 kg/m³, 8 m/s and 0.5 m² respectively. The velocity at another section having area of 1 m² and density of 4 kg/m³ will be', '3 m/s', '2 m/s', '4 m/s', '1 m/s', 1, 'Continuity: ρ1 A1 V1 = ρ2 A2 V2 => 3×0.5×8 = 4×1×V2 => V2 = 3 m/s.', 'medium'),
('e33338c9-740c-48c4-914b-2cca3e9c1668'::uuid, '64289b52-861b-4a49-9286-4c4196691af7'::uuid, '9b40396e-3ed0-47ab-b981-52f6a8e6cdd3'::uuid, 2023, 'Paper-I', 'A graph showing variations of discharge with time a particular point of stream is called as', 'Hydrograph', 'Hyetograph', 'Hygrograph', 'Isohyt', 1, 'Hydrograph plots discharge vs time.', 'medium'),
('e33338c9-740c-48c4-914b-2cca3e9c1668'::uuid, 'a8556419-0986-4502-80b2-78b7defb8990'::uuid, 'ec71764c-6040-47e0-bbc1-9777aafbeec7'::uuid, 2023, 'Paper-I', 'Pascal-second is the unit of', 'kinematic viscosity', 'pressure', 'dynamic viscosity', 'surface tension', 3, 'Pascal-second (Pa·s) is unit of dynamic viscosity.', 'medium'),
('e33338c9-740c-48c4-914b-2cca3e9c1668'::uuid, 'cd7b170d-eba3-4a13-8b23-3c318071b538'::uuid, '63b1aa41-9022-4bff-b5b8-0aa71ec874fd'::uuid, 2023, 'Paper-I', 'The maximum effective slenderness ratio value of a tension member in which a reversal of direct stress occurs due to loads other than wind or seismic forces, is', '400', '350', '180', '250', 3, 'For tension members with stress reversal, slenderness ratio ≤ 180.', 'medium'),
('e33338c9-740c-48c4-914b-2cca3e9c1668'::uuid, 'a3efd61d-542a-4076-8ffe-631b227f0239'::uuid, '880c7ee1-0204-4a42-979f-338ca32f84be'::uuid, 2023, 'Paper-I', 'First class bricks are used for', 'Boundary walls', 'Brick ballast in R.C.C.', 'Low height walls and soak pit walls', 'Pavements and Load bearing walls', 4, 'First class bricks are suitable for load bearing walls.', 'medium'),
('e33338c9-740c-48c4-914b-2cca3e9c1668'::uuid, 'e7eaeaa0-d839-4490-abed-c71027b61424'::uuid, '1bba627d-75a7-47e9-8413-f09905572b33'::uuid, 2023, 'Paper-I', 'What is the magnitude of coefficient of thermal expansion for the Cement Concrete ?', '6×10⁻⁶/°C to 8×10⁻⁶/°C', '18×10⁻⁶/°C to 20×10⁻⁶/°C', '12×10⁻⁶/°C to 14×10⁻⁶/°C', '8×10⁻⁶/°C to 10×10⁻⁶/°C', 3, 'Concrete thermal expansion coefficient is about 10-12×10⁻⁶/°C; option 3 (12-14) is close but actually 10-12. I''ll pick 3 as best.', 'medium'),
('e33338c9-740c-48c4-914b-2cca3e9c1668'::uuid, 'a8556419-0986-4502-80b2-78b7defb8990'::uuid, 'ec71764c-6040-47e0-bbc1-9777aafbeec7'::uuid, 2023, 'Paper-I', 'If the dynamic viscosity of a fluid is 0.5 poise and specific gravity is 0.5, then the kinematic viscosity of that fluid in stokes is', '0.50', '0.25', '1.0', '1.5', 3, 'ν = μ/ρ; μ=0.05 Pa.s, ρ=500 kg/m³, ν=1e-4 m²/s = 1 stoke.', 'medium'),
('e33338c9-740c-48c4-914b-2cca3e9c1668'::uuid, '3f275622-18e3-40ce-a134-ec660b48190c'::uuid, 'f28c858a-cf0c-482e-a112-8845927e82f4'::uuid, 2023, 'Paper-I', 'The whole circle bearing of P and Q are 24°30'' and 327°24'' respectively. Then which of the following statements about the quadrantal bearing is/are correct ? A. The quadrantal bearing of P is N 24°30'' E B. The quadrantal bearing of P is S 24°30'' W C. The quadrantal bearing of Q is N 32°36'' W D. The quadrantal bearing of Q is S 32°36'' E Choose the correct option', 'B and D', 'A and C', 'A and D', 'B and C', 2, 'P: N 24°30'' E; Q: N 32°36'' W.', 'medium'),
('e33338c9-740c-48c4-914b-2cca3e9c1668'::uuid, 'aee3c24f-8b41-461f-8e64-e9544a04c1b6'::uuid, '4cf00bbd-c0d6-49dd-88a5-505bae0ef9ab'::uuid, 2023, 'Paper-I', 'In long and short wall method of estimation, the length of long wall is the centre to centre distance between the walls and', 'half breadth of wall on each side', 'breadth of the wall on each side', 'one fourth breadth of wall on each side', 'one third breadth of wall on each side', 1, 'Long wall length = centre to centre + breadth of wall (half on each side).', 'medium'),
('e33338c9-740c-48c4-914b-2cca3e9c1668'::uuid, 'a3efd61d-542a-4076-8ffe-631b227f0239'::uuid, '880c7ee1-0204-4a42-979f-338ca32f84be'::uuid, 2023, 'Paper-I', 'Artificial stone is also known as :', 'Plastic stone', 'Ashlar stone', 'Igneous stone', 'Casted stone', 4, 'Artificial stone is also called cast stone.', 'medium')
